---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Security & Privacy — Meridian',
  description:
    'Meridian is anonymous by design: it never collects your name, broker credentials, account numbers, or funds. Data used to improve the product and for research is anonymized and never sold — and you can opt out. Understand exactly what the software does and does not do.',
  robots: { index: true, follow: true },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-14">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3" style="color:var(--aw-color-primary);">Security & Privacy</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight tracking-tight mb-5">
          Anonymous<br />by design.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
          Meridian runs inside NinjaTrader 8 on your Windows PC. It never collects your name, broker
          credentials, account numbers, or funds. To improve the product and run research on trading
          discipline, it transmits <strong>anonymized</strong> records of your trading activity and the
          behavioral signals it computes — tied only to a random identifier, never your identity, never
          sold. You can opt out at any time. See the
          <a href="/data-research" class="text-emerald-700 underline hover:text-emerald-900">Data &amp; Research Notice</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 1: What Meridian stores -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What Meridian stores — and where</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Session behavioral data</strong> — PSI scores, signal readings, composure grades, trade counts, and timestamps. Stored in a local database on your Windows PC.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Your configuration</strong> — Guard rules, session parameters, baseline preferences. Stored locally in NinjaTrader's standard add-on data path.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Up to 5 years of history</strong> — all stored on your machine. Uninstalling Meridian removes the software; your local data files remain under your control unless you delete them.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: What it does NOT do -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What Meridian does not do</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-zinc-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Never collects identifying or financial data</strong> — no name, broker credentials, account numbers, card details, or funds. Anonymized trading and behavioral records used for product improvement and research are tied only to a random identifier, never sold, and you can opt out anytime.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-zinc-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Does not require broker credentials</strong> — Meridian reads execution data from NinjaTrader's internal data layer, not directly from your broker's API. No passwords or API keys are ever passed to Meridian.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-zinc-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Optional auto-liquidation</strong> — Guard can block new order entry and, at the highest enforcement level, disconnect the broker connection. You can configure Guard to optionally force-close open trades, or choose to manage them yourself.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-zinc-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">Does not provide trading signals</strong> — PSI is a behavioral stability score, not a directional indicator. Meridian generates no buy or sell signals and offers no investment advice.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-zinc-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-800">No third-party ad tracking or profiling</strong> — we do not sell your data or use it for advertising. The only data we collect is anonymized trading/behavioral data for product improvement and research, which you can turn off.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: The only external connection -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">External connections</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Meridian makes two kinds of external request. <strong class="text-zinc-800">License validation via Whop</strong>
          (on startup) contains only a license identifier — no trade data and no personally identifiable information.
          <strong class="text-zinc-800">Anonymized research upload</strong> sends trading and behavioral records tied only to
          a random identifier (no name, credentials, account numbers, or funds) over HTTPS — used solely to improve the
          product and for research, never sold, and <strong class="text-zinc-800">fully optional</strong> (the product works
          even if it is blocked, and you can opt out). Details: <a href="/data-research" class="text-emerald-700 underline hover:text-emerald-900">Data &amp; Research Notice</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          If you have questions about how Whop handles subscription data, their privacy policy is available at
          <a href="https://whop.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-emerald-700 underline hover:text-emerald-900">whop.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Guard enforcement boundaries -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What Guard enforces — and what it cannot touch</h2>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 p-5 text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p><strong class="text-zinc-800">Guard blocks new order entry</strong> at the NinjaTrader platform level when a configured threshold is crossed. It intercepts the order before it is submitted — it does not interfere with orders already in the market.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-zinc-800">Guard offers optional auto-liquidation.</strong> If Guard locks new entries while you have a live trade, you can configure it to automatically close open positions or choose to exit that trade manually through NinjaTrader.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-zinc-800">Broker disconnect mode</strong> (the highest enforcement level) terminates NinjaTrader's broker connection. This prevents all new order activity — including exits — until you reconnect. This mode is an advanced option intended for situations where full disengagement from the market is desired. It should be understood and tested in simulation before being used live.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: NinjaTrader relationship -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Relationship to NinjaTrader</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Meridian is an <strong class="text-zinc-800">Official NinjaTrader Ecosystem Vendor</strong>. Our application,
          our website, our social channels, and the Meridian NT8 add-on itself have been reviewed and approved by
          NinjaTrader's Compliance, QA, and Executive teams before being listed in the NinjaTrader Ecosystem.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          Meridian is operated by an independent company and is a third-party add-on for NinjaTrader 8 &mdash;
          NinjaTrader® is a registered trademark of NinjaTrader LLC, and Meridian is not owned by NinjaTrader LLC.
          Meridian installs through NinjaTrader's standard add-on import process and operates within the permissions
          that NinjaTrader makes available to all approved Ecosystem developers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <div class="border-t border-zinc-100 pt-10">
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
          Questions about data handling or security?
          <a href="/support" class="text-emerald-700 underline hover:text-emerald-900">Contact us</a> —
          we'll get back to you within 24 hours.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
